01:04:15,880 --> 01:04:18,880
 unfortunately passed away recently from cancer,

1004
01:04:18,880 --> 01:04:21,880
 but leaves behind a legacy of amazing books and teaching.

1005
01:04:21,880 --> 01:04:25,880
 One of the great pastors in the city of New York, he wrote it this way.

1006
01:04:25,880 --> 01:04:29,880
 He said, "Fear-based confession and repentance makes us hate ourselves.

1007
01:04:29,880 --> 01:04:34,880
 We feel really bad, but joy-based confession and repentance makes us hate sin."

1008
01:04:34,880 --> 01:04:36,880
 Do you see the difference?

1009
01:04:36,880 --> 01:04:40,880
 And some of you in this room, you come in today hating yourself.

1010
01:04:40,880 --> 01:04:43,880
 You come in feeling really bad about yourself.

1011
01:04:43,880 --> 01:04:47,880
 You're so wallowing in guilt and shame

1012
01:04:47,880 --> 01:04:49,880
 and you think God hates you too.

1013
01:04:49,880 --> 01:04:51,880
 You think God is angry at you, upset at you.

1014
01:04:51,880 --> 01:04:54,880
 You think God is distant from you.

1015
01:04:54,880 --> 01:04:58,880
 And we need to shift our mentality here to realize that there is a hate at work,

1016
01:04:58,880 --> 01:05:00,880
 but it's not a hate of ourselves.

1017
01:05:00,880 --> 01:05:04,880
 It's a hate of the impact and the entanglement of sin

1018
01:05:04,880 --> 01:05:08,880
 and the joy of knowing a Christ who can free us from that

1019
01:05:08,880 --> 01:05:15,880
 and set us back into a new place, a place of love and joy and grace and hope.

1020
01:05:15,880 --> 01:05:19,880
 So you need to understand that confession and repentance

1021
01:05:19,880 --> 01:05:23,880
 is actually the truest form of worship that we have.

1022
01:05:23,880 --> 01:05:25,880
 Because think about it.

1023
01:05:25,880 --> 01:05:29,880
 If worship is about ascribing glory to Christ,

1024
01:05:29,880 --> 01:05:34,880
 the greatest glory that Christ will ever do for you is to save you.

1025
01:05:34,880 --> 01:05:38,880
 It is, in other words, to deal with the sin issue in your life.

1026
01:05:38,880 --> 01:05:41,880
 It is to free you from sin and brokenness

1027
01:05:41,880 --> 01:05:44,880
 and bring you back into right relationship with Christ

1028
01:05:44,880 --> 01:05:46,880
 and reconcile you with Him.

1029
01:05:46,880 --> 01:05:51,880
 And because of that, our joy of confession and repentance

1030
01:05:51,880 --> 01:05:53,880
 is actually an act of worship.

1031
01:05:53,880 --> 01:05:58,880
 It's actually a way for us to honor and to glorify what Christ has done on the cross.

1032
01:05:58,880 --> 01:06:03,880
 And when we fail to repent and confess, when we hold on to sin,

1033
01:06:03,880 --> 01:06:05,880
 we're actually doing the opposite.

1034
01:06:05,880 --> 01:06:08,880
 We're not honoring the work that the cross has provided for us,

1035
01:06:08,880 --> 01:06:13,880
 and instead we're holding on to our brokenness as if the cross hasn't happened.

1036
01:06:13,880 --> 01:06:16,880
 But the cross has happened. You have been set free.

1037
01:06:16,880 --> 01:06:20,880
 And what that means is that sin no longer has a grip on you.

1038
01:06:20,880 --> 01:06:23,880
 Sin does not get the final say. Amen?

1039
01:06:23,880 --> 01:06:26,880
 It does not get the final say in your life.

1040
01:06:26,880 --> 01:06:28,880
 And because it no longer has the final say,

1041
01:06:28,880 --> 01:06:31,880
 when we engage in confession and repentance,

1042
01:06:31,880 --> 01:06:37,880
 we're aligning our belief to the reality that the cross is louder than sin.

1043
01:06:37,880 --> 01:06:40,880
 Whoa, that was cool.

1044
01:06:40,880 --> 01:06:44,880
 The cross is louder than sin.

1045
01:06:44,880 --> 01:06:48,880
 Are you tracking with this?

1046
01:06:48,880 --> 01:06:53,880
 I've noticed in my life as I've made the shift from thinking about repentance and confession

1047
01:06:53,880 --> 01:06:56,880
 from a fear place, from a place of guilt and shame,

1048
01:06:56,880 --> 01:07:00,880
 to a place of honor and joy and ultimately love,

1049
01:07:00,880 --> 01:07:03,880
 I've noticed a lot of changes in my life.

1050
01:07:03,880 --> 01:07:08,880
 I've noticed that when I'm in sin, which I am at times,

1051
01:07:08,880 --> 01:07:12,880
 when I'm in a place of sin, before when it was fear-based,

1052
01:07:12,880 --> 01:07:14,880
 I felt a lot of condemnation.

1053
01:07:14,880 --> 01:07:17,880
 Now when it's joy-based, I feel a lot of conviction.

1054
01:07:17,880 --> 01:07:20,880
 And conviction enables me to deal with that sin.

1055
01:07:20,880 --> 01:07:23,880
 Condemnation makes me feel bad about it. Are you with me?

1056
01:07:23,880 --> 01:07:26,880
 I've noticed when I've made the shift that before,

1057
01:07:26,880 --> 01:07:30,880
 when I had a fear-based relationship with confession and repentance,

1058
01:07:30,880 --> 01:07:33,880
 I noticed that I would often blame God.

1059
01:07:33,880 --> 01:07:39,880
 Now I find myself within the joy aspect, actually wanting to align with God

1060
01:07:39,880 --> 01:07:43,880
 and how He sees the reality that's happening in my life.

1061
01:07:43,880 --> 01:07:49,880
 I've noticed before that I would find myself being angry at myself.

1062
01:07:49,880 --> 01:07:54,880
 I now find myself through a joy-based confession and repentance,

1063
01:07:54,880 --> 01:07:57,880
 finding myself humbled.

1064
01:07:57,880 --> 01:07:59,880
 It's a different experience.

1065
01:07:59,880 --> 01:08:01,880
 I still recognize the sin and I'm not proud of it.

1066
01:08:01,880 --> 01:08:05,880
 But rather than feeling like I'm beating myself up about it,

1067
01:08:05,880 --> 01:08:09,880
 I'm able to humble myself into the hands of the Lord

1068
01:08:09,880 --> 01:08:12,880
 and ask Him to deal with what only He can deal with it,

1069
01:08:12,880 --> 01:08:15,880
 because my local anesthetic can't touch it.

1070
01:08:15,880 --> 01:08:22,880
 But His Valium, the Holy Spirit, the blood of Jesus on the cross,

1071
01:08:22,880 --> 01:08:25,880
 can truly get to the root. Are you tracking with this?

1072
01:08:25,880 --> 01:08:30,880
 David, one of the great psalmists, writes so beautifully of this whole process.

1073
01:08:30,880 --> 01:08:33,880
 I want to just sit us in Psalm 32 for a little bit

1074
01:08:33,880 --> 01:08:36,880
 as I unpack this idea a bit more with you guys.

1075
01:08:36,880 --> 01:08:39,880
 David's an interesting man, because when we hear of David in the Old Testament,

1076
01:08:39,880 --> 01:08:42,880
 we often think of David as this amazing guy,

1077
01:08:42,880 --> 01:08:44,880
 this guy that had the idea for the temple,

1078
01:08:44,880 --> 01:08:48,880
 a great leader who established Israel into Jerusalem.

1079
01:08:48,880 --> 01:08:51,880
 Christ, we know, comes from the Davidic line.

1080
01:08:51,880 --> 01:08:54,880
 Often the Scriptures talk about this Davidic dynasty,

1081
01:08:54,880 --> 01:08:56,880
 that the Messiah would come from the house of David.

1082
01:08:56,880 --> 01:09:00,880
 So David has a lot of sense of revere and honor in the Old Testament,

1083
01:09:00,880 --> 01:09:03,880
 but the reality is David was a very broken man.

1084
01:09:03,880 --> 01:09:06,880
 David was a sinner. He was a deep sinner.

1085
01:09:06,880 --> 01:09:10,880
 He was a man who committed murder. He was a man who committed rape.

1086
01:09:10,880 --> 01:09:13,880
 He had a lot of lust issues. He had a lot of sexual brokenness in his life.

1087
01:09:13,880 --> 01:09:16,880
 He is not a perfect person.

1088
01:09:16,880 --> 01:09:19,880
 And I want to encourage you that there are no perfect people in this room.

1089
01:09:19,880 --> 01:09:22,880
 There are no perfect people here.

1090
01:09:22,880 --> 01:09:25,880
 And the vine celebrates the beauty of the fact that none of us are perfect,

1091
01:09:25,880 --> 01:09:27,880
 but we have a perfect Savior.

1092
01:09:27,880 --> 01:09:31,880
 And that's the invitation we have to a God who is so good.

1093
01:09:31,880 --> 01:09:35,880
 Now listen to how David in his brokenness, who knows God so well,

1094
01:09:35,880 --> 01:09:39,880
 notice what he says. He says, "Blessed is he whose transgressions are forgiven."

1095
01:09:39,880 --> 01:09:42,880
 That's sins. "Whose sins are forgiven, whose sins are covered.

1096
01:09:42,880 --> 01:09:46,880
 Blessed is the one whose sins the Lord no longer counts against him

1097
01:09:46,880 --> 01:09:48,880
 and whose spirit is no deceit." Notice how he starts.

1098
01:09:48,880 --> 01:09:51,880
 He says, "You need to understand that you're blessed,

1099
01:09:51,880 --> 01:09:55,880
 that you're blessed when the Lord doesn't hold any sin against you.

1100
01:09:55,880 --> 01:09:58,880
 You're blessed when you're in a relationship with God

1101
01:09:58,880 --> 01:10:00,880
 where he sees you through the blood of Jesus.

1102
01:10:00,880 --> 01:10:03,880
 You're blessed because you live on this side of the cross of Calvary.

1103
01:10:03,880 --> 01:10:07,880
 You're blessed because you have a place to bring your brokenness and bring your sin.

1104
01:10:07,880 --> 01:10:10,880
 That's a place of blessing. Blessing here means flourishing.

1105
01:10:10,880 --> 01:10:15,880
 It means life. It means abundancy. It means growth. It means goodness.

1106
01:10:15,880 --> 01:10:19,880
 That's how David starts. He says, "You need to understand how God sees you

1107
01:10:19,880 --> 01:10:22,880
 through the cross of Jesus. You are blessed.

1108
01:10:22,880 --> 01:10:27,880
 Blessed are those whose sins are forgiven and your sins are forgiven because of Christ."

1109
01:10:27,880 --> 01:10:30,880
 That's a beautiful place to start.

1110
01:10:30,880 --> 01:10:33,880
 In other words, when we're talking about confession, repentance, and sin,

1111
01:10:33,880 --> 01:10:37,880
 our starting point should not be, "Oh, I'm bad. I'm terrible. I'm horrible."

1112
01:10:37,880 --> 01:10:41,880
 Our starting point should be, "I'm blessed because I have the opportunity to be redeemed.

1113
01:10:41,880 --> 01:10:45,880
 I have the opportunity to be reconciled. I have the opportunity to be changed."

1114
01:10:45,880 --> 01:10:48,880
 Are you with me? That's the starting point for us.

1115
01:10:48,880 --> 01:10:52,880
 We are blessed. That doesn't mean that we don't still have sin.

1116
01:10:52,880 --> 01:10:55,880
 It doesn't mean that we don't need to deal with some things.

1117
01:10:55,880 --> 01:10:58,880
 It doesn't mean that we can't just go, "Oh, okay, whatever."

1118
01:10:58,880 --> 01:11:00,880
 We'll get on to that in a moment.

1119
01:11:00,880 --> 01:11:04,880
 But your starting point is you're blessed because you have an opportunity

1120
01:11:04,880 --> 01:11:08,880
 to fully get untangled. Are you with me?

1121
01:11:08,880 --> 01:11:12,880
 This is really important because the whole of Scripture speaks this way.

1122
01:11:12,880 --> 01:11:15,880
 I love actually, let me just jump to 1 John.

1123
01:11:15,880 --> 01:11:20,880
 Right at the end of the New Testament, 1 John puts it really quite powerfully in verse 9.

1124
01:11:20,880 --> 01:11:25,880
 He says, "If we confess our sins, He is faithful and just and will forgive our sins

1125
01:11:25,880 --> 01:11:30,880
 and purify us from all unrighteousness." There's the concept, "Purify us."

1126
01:11:30,880 --> 01:11:34,880
 If we confess our sins, He is faithful to forgive.

1127
01:11:34,880 --> 01:11:38,880
 Now, anyone in this room right now, whatever it is that you've brought in today,

1128
01:11:38,880 --> 01:11:42,880
 no matter what's going on in your life, no matter what sin that you know you're carrying,

1129
01:11:42,880 --> 01:11:45,880
 no matter what brokenness, no matter you know what you've done in your past,

1130
01:11:45,880 --> 01:11:49,880
 none of that is unforgivable. Are you with me?

1131
01:11:49,880 --> 01:11:52,880
 Every single sin that you're carrying in your heart, in your life,

1132
01:11:52,880 --> 01:11:58,880
 anything that's ever happened, you can be cleansed from that because Christ is faithful.

1133
01:11:58,880 --> 01:12:01,880
 He doesn't say, "I'm just going to pop it up, zip you out. It's fine."

1134
01:12:01,880 --> 01:12:04,880
 He doesn't treat it lightly. He says, "I'm going to get into the root of it.

1135
01:12:04,880 --> 01:12:08,880
 I am faithful and the cross has dealt with it and you can know times of refleshing.

1136
01:12:08,880 --> 01:12:11,880
 You are blessed."

1137
01:12:11,880 --> 01:12:17,880
 Now, this is a great joy, but David goes on to do something that's really important.

1138
01:12:17,880 --> 01:12:21,880
 He goes on to say, "The problem we have as Christians, though,

1139
01:12:21,880 --> 01:12:25,880
 is that even though we have this ability to confess and repent,

1140
01:12:25,880 --> 01:12:30,880
 our issue is we very rarely do so."

1141
01:12:30,880 --> 01:12:36,880
 Yeah, not the best, but it's not really hurting anyone.

1142
01:12:36,880 --> 01:12:40,880
 Nobody knows about it. I've gotten away with it for some time.

1143
01:12:40,880 --> 01:12:43,880
 I guess I'll just keep getting on with it.

1144
01:12:43,880 --> 01:12:47,880
 It's very easy for us, I think, as Christians to recognize that there is this brokenness in us

1145
01:12:47,880 --> 01:12:49,880
 and to hold on to it.

1146
01:12:49,880 --> 01:12:54,880
 I want you to hear how David describes what it is to hold on to unconfessed sin.

1147
01:12:54,880 --> 01:13:00,880
 Verse 3 and 4, "When I kept silent, when I just kind of went, 'Meh, no big deal,'

1148
01:13:00,880 --> 01:13:01,880
 here's what happened.

1149
01:13:01,880 --> 01:13:05,880
 My bones wasted away, though through my groaning all day long,

1150
01:13:05,880 --> 01:13:08,880
 for day and night your hand was heavy upon me.

1151
01:13:08,880 --> 01:13:12,880
 My strength was sapped as in the summer heat," or the heat of the summer.

1152
01:13:12,880 --> 01:13:16,880
 He says, "Here's how it felt when I didn't confess, when I didn't repent,

1153
01:13:16,880 --> 01:13:21,880
 when I realized that I'm blessed, but the problem is I held on to my sin

1154
01:13:21,880 --> 01:13:22,880
 and I remained silent.

1155
01:13:22,880 --> 01:13:26,880
 And here's what it felt like. It felt like my bones were wasting away."

1156
01:13:26,880 --> 01:13:29,880
 I wonder if anybody resonates with that in this room, because I know I do.

1157
01:13:29,880 --> 01:13:31,880
 "It felt like my bones were wasting away.

1158
01:13:31,880 --> 01:13:33,880
 It felt like I was groaning all day long.

1159
01:13:33,880 --> 01:13:37,880
 It felt like I had a heaviness, a yoke upon me.

1160
01:13:37,880 --> 01:13:40,880
 It felt like I was in Hong Kong in the middle of the summer,

1161
01:13:40,880 --> 01:13:42,880
 and it was crazy humidity, and I was wearing too many clothes,

1162
01:13:42,880 --> 01:13:46,880
 and I'm sweaty, and I'm tired, and I'm worn out, and I just want to go home.

1163
01:13:46,880 --> 01:13:48,880
 That's what it feels like.

1164
01:13:48,880 --> 01:13:51,880
 When I kept silent, that was what my life was like."

1165
01:13:51,880 --> 01:13:53,880
 And I want you to see what David is doing.

1166
01:13:53,880 --> 01:13:54,880
 Listen to this. This is really important.

1167
01:13:54,880 --> 01:13:56,880
 Here's what David's doing in this psalm.

1168
01:13:56,880 --> 01:14:00,880
 He's setting up two true realities, the reality of being blessed,

1169
01:14:00,880 --> 01:14:04,880
 because you have your sins forgiven, and the reality of holding on to your sins

1170
01:14:04,880 --> 01:14:07,880
 and feeling anything other than being blessed. Are you with me?

1171
01:14:07,880 --> 01:14:10,880
 And David is basically saying, "Choose one of those things,"

1172
01:14:10,880 --> 01:14:13,880
 because every single human being is going to be in one of those things.

1173
01:14:13,880 --> 01:14:15,880
 You're either blessed because you know that your sins are forgiven,

1174
01:14:15,880 --> 01:14:17,880
 and you're finding refreshing times in the Lord,

1175
01:14:17,880 --> 01:14:20,880
 or your bones are wasting away, and there's this groaning in you,

1176
01:14:20,880 --> 01:14:25,880
 and a heaviness upon you, and it feels like your energy is sapped from the summer heat.

1177
01:14:25,880 --> 01:14:30,880
 He's like, "Those are the two realities in life you can choose."

1178
01:14:30,880 --> 01:14:35,880
 "When I kept silent, that was my choice. My bones wasted away.

1179
01:14:35,880 --> 01:14:41,880
 When I confessed, something changed. Something happened."

1180
01:14:41,880 --> 01:14:45,880
 It's very easy for us, however, to remain silent.

1181
01:14:45,880 --> 01:14:48,880
 And here's the question we need to ask ourselves this morning.

1182
01:14:48,880 --> 01:14:55,880
 Why do we as Christians, when we understand the benefits of confession and repentance,

1183
01:14:55,880 --> 01:14:59,880
 very often remain silent?

1184
01:14:59,880 --> 01:15:03,880
 Why is it that we don't always confess and repent?

1185
01:15:03,880 --> 01:15:07,880
 Let me offer you a couple of quick thoughts.

1186
01:15:07,880 --> 01:15:12,880
 I think one of the reasons why we don't is because we actually deny the reality of sin.

1187
01:15:12,880 --> 01:15:14,880
 We actually just deny it.

1188
01:15:14,880 --> 01:15:18,880
 We actually think we don't call it sin. We call it, "Ah, just a little mistake."

1189
01:15:18,880 --> 01:15:25,880
 Or we look in the mirror like I did and go, "Ah, yeah. Nah. Don't need to do anything."

1190
01:15:25,880 --> 01:15:27,880
 And we actually deny the reality of our sin.

1191
01:15:27,880 --> 01:15:32,880
 One of the very first things we need to do is actually be honest with ourselves about what it is that we carry.

1192
01:15:32,880 --> 01:15:37,880
 That doesn't mean it has to come with emotions of guilt and shame and wrath and anger.

1193
01:15:37,880 --> 01:15:39,880
 It doesn't mean that we have to go there.

1194
01:15:39,880 --> 01:15:43,880
 But we have to kind of say to ourselves, "I recognize that there is a brokenness I'm carrying."

1195
01:15:43,880 --> 01:15:47,880
 "And that brokenness is not right. I recognize that it breaks the heart of God."

1196
01:15:47,880 --> 01:15:49,880
 "I recognize that this is not what I've been created for."

1197
01:15:49,880 --> 01:15:52,880
 "And I recognize that there's another way that I could be living."

1198
01:15:52,880 --> 01:15:55,880
 We have to take seriously the reality of our sin.

1199
01:15:55,880 --> 01:15:58,880
 I eventually had to deal with that thing on my back.

1200
01:15:58,880 --> 01:16:01,880
 This is what confession is, my friends.

1201
01:16:01,880 --> 01:16:04,880
 Confession is taking ownership of our sin.

1202
01:16:04,880 --> 01:16:13,880
 You see, you cannot repent of sin until you have first confessed your sin.

1203
01:16:13,880 --> 01:16:18,880
 Repentance of sin, the changing from it, and being back in right relationship with God,

1204
01:16:18,880 --> 01:16:21,880
 only happens when we take ownership of our sin.

1205
01:16:21,880 --> 01:16:26,880
 When we confess it, confession is saying, "Yeah, I recognize that there is this sin in my life."

1206
01:16:26,880 --> 01:16:30,880
 It's actually verbalizing in our hearts or even out loud with others

1207
01:16:30,880 --> 01:16:34,880
 that there is a brokenness that we're dealing with and we cannot deal with on our own.

1208
01:16:34,880 --> 01:16:39,880
 You cannot have repentance of sin until there is first confession of sin.

1209
01:16:39,880 --> 01:16:40,880
 Does that make sense?

1210
01:16:40,880 --> 01:16:44,880
 And one of the reasons why I think we don't confess is we don't take that part seriously enough.

1211
01:16:44,880 --> 01:16:47,880
 We deny the reality of our sin.

1212
01:16:47,880 --> 01:16:50,880
 I think the second reason why we don't confess and repent sometimes

1213
01:16:50,880 --> 01:16:56,880
 is because we fail to find true sorrow in us for our sin.

1214
01:16:56,880 --> 01:16:59,880
 It's interesting, the word "confession" in the Greek in the New Testament

1215
01:16:59,880 --> 01:17:04,880
 is actually the word homo legeo.

1216
01:17:04,880 --> 01:17:06,880
 And homo legeo is two words broken down.

1217
01:17:06,880 --> 01:17:10,880
 Homos means "the same," and legeo means "to speak."

1218
01:17:10,880 --> 01:17:15,880
 And it's really interesting that the Bible would use this word to talk about the act of confession,

1219
01:17:15,880 --> 01:17:23,880
 because really what it's saying is that the act of confession is to speak the same thing about sin as God does.

1220
01:17:23,880 --> 01:17:28,880
 It is to say the same thing about sin as God does.

1221
01:17:28,880 --> 01:17:31,880
 And here's what God says about sin.

1222
01:17:31,880 --> 01:17:33,880
 Sin breaks relationship.

1223
01:17:33,880 --> 01:17:36,880
 Sin breaks relationship with one another, and it breaks relationship with Him.

1224
01:17:36,880 --> 01:17:40,880
 Sin breaks His heart, because He sees what He has created you for,

1225
